  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0ba4 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b87\u0baf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8 -  \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b86\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Schools not functioning due to vague announcement by the government - Sri Lanka Tamil Teachers Association",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Tamil Teachers' Union (SLTTU) has pointed out that due to the government's ambiguous announcement, teacher and student credit was low in most schools in the country on the 27th and most schools were not functioning.",
        "This is stated in the statement issued by the Sri Lanka Tamil Teachers Association",
        "In view of such a situation, the government's confusing announcement of running schools for three days and five days, favorable notice to teachers that non-attending teachers cannot be considered as private holidays, inconvenience to transport for principal teachers, irregular fuel distribution, strike by EPF staff, dangerous announcement of fuel shortage by the Minister of Energy. We had appealed to all of us to avoid going to school until the traffic was light.",
        "Accordingly many of the schools in the country which do not have transport routes do not accept our request and do not go to school. The executive members and zonal secretaries of our association have confirmed that the enrollment of students was low while a few school principals forcibly invited Asians.",
        "Without such a situation continuing, the government should immediately address the issue of children's education, fuel supply for teachers and transport routes. Otherwise, the entire school will be closed for a long time."
      ],
